Math.Equation

Class Node

  • java.lang.Object
    • Math.Equation.Node
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Math.MathObject
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    FinalNode

    public class Node
extends java.lang.Object
implements Math.MathObject
    A class that represents either a custom function, an inbuilt function, an operation, or a group of tokens.

    0.1

      • condeseNodes

        public static java.lang.Object[] condeseNodes(int pos,
                                              Node n,
                                              java.util.ArrayList<Token> pTokens)
        Condenses functions and groups together into a single node. Creates 1-length nodes for operations and vars / nums. Note that this is only ever used with fixNodes, generateNodes and completeNodes.
        Parameters:
        pos - The position to start condensing nodes form.
        n - The "parent" node that any newly generated nodes will be put into.
        pTokens - The list of tokens that will be put into nodes.
        Returns:
        The return type might seem odd, however, it always returns an updated pos as argument 1, and the new node to add as argument 2.

      • completeNodes

        public static Node completeNodes(Node pNode)
        Creates a master node using the pNode as a starting point by applying the Order of Operations. Note: pNode should already have been condensed via condeseNodes, and fixed via fixNodes.
        Parameters:
        pNode - The node that will be used to generate the new hierarchically-structured master node.
        Returns:
        The "master" node - that is, the node to control all other nodes. HAH - LOTR reference.

      • getD

        public Node getD(int i)
        Goes down i layers, or until a group / function is hit to get the last node in the subNode list. Note: if the current node is a FinalNode, and getD is called, it will just return itself.
        For example, getting the very last node in subNodes (subNode.get(subNode.size() - 1))) is "going down one layer". Don't know how to explain much better.
        Parameters:
        i - The amount of layers to go down.
        Returns:
        The final node at layer i. Doesn't check to see if i is a valid layer.

      • getD

        public Node getD(int i,
                 boolean pOver)
        Goes down i layers, or until a group / function is hit if pOver is false. to get the last node in the subNode list. Note: if the current node is a FinalNode, and getD is called, it will just return itself.
        For example, getting the very last node in subNodes (subNode.get(subNode.size() - 1))) is "going down one layer". Don't know how to explain much better.
        Parameters:
        i - The amount of layers to go down.
        pOver - Whether or not it will "override", and continue going down if a group is encountered.
        Returns:
        The final node at layer i. Doesn't check to see if i is a valid layer.
